pulfalight.title: Index direct_content_warning_ssm and use it for Figgy.
Use actual component ids (with dots) in urls

comments.body:
There are two different syntaxes being used in PulfaLight that could complicate the regular expressions needed to fix:
1. https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/AC198-05_c1791
2. https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C1491_c87307-37697

We will want to write tests to ensure both of these syntaxes resolve.

I think that in both cases the dash is replacing a dot, and the underscore is part of the component id. Here's the figgy record for the first example in the previous comment https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/994e4d15-d6e9-49bd-b483-6cd8fd63a810/
